<table class="form" border="1">
  <tr>
    <td>
      View Name:
    </td>
    <td>
      <%= f.text_field :name, :class=>'field' %>
      <%= hidden_field_tag :next, '/views' %>
      <%= link_to_function 'Done', "$('next').value = '/views';$('view_form').submit();", :class => 'button' %>
      <%= link_to_function 'Go To View', "$('next').value = '/directory/change_view?view_id=#{@view.id}';$('view_form').submit();", :class => 'button' %>
<!--  ============= BEGIN Layout column choices ============== -->
<p>The following columns are currently a part of this view. To reorder them, 
simply click and drag the column where you'd like it to be. To remove a column 
from the view, simply click on the red 'x' on that row. <strong>Changes are 
saved automatically!</strong></p>
<ul id="column_list">
	<% @view.sitrack_view_columns.each do |column| -%>
		<li id="column_<%=column.id%>">
				<%=link_to_remote image_tag('x.png', :border => 0), 
						:url => {:action => :remove_column, :view_column_id => column.id}%>
				&nbsp;&nbsp;<%=column.sitrack_column.name%>
		</li>
	<% end -%>
</ul>
<p>The columns listed below are not currently part of your view. To add one 
of the columns below to your view simply click on it. When you click on it 
it will jump to the bottom of the list above. Once it's there you can click 
and drag it where you'd like the column to go.
<ul id="unused_column_list">
<% @unused_columns.each do |column| -%>
	<li id="unused_<%=column.id%>">
			<%= link_to column.name, 
					{:action => :add_column, :id => @view.id, :column_id => column.id},
					{:remote => true}%>
	</li>
<% end -%>
</ul>
